  "detailed_description": [
    {
      "heading": "Enhanced Performance and Connectivity",
      "text": "The MikroTik FiberBox Plus, model CRS305-1G-4S+OUT, represents a significant evolution from its predecessors, offering robust performance in a rugged outdoor-ready package. This latest iteration features an enhanced ARM CPU, increased RAM, and four 10-Gigabit SFP+ ports, providing fast and reliable fiber connectivity tailored for budget-conscious users without the limitations of Ethernet distance constraints."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Advanced Networking Features",
      "text": "Running on MikroTik's RouterOS v7 or SwOS, the FiberBox Plus allows for comprehensive network management and configuration. Users can leverage advanced Layer 3 routing features, firewall setups, and bandwidth management. The system's flexibility is also highlighted by its multiple SFP+ ports which can be configured to manage different data streams or link types, from connecting payment and inventory servers in a food court to providing a fiber backbone to residential guest houses."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Flexible Powering Options",
      "text": "FiberBox Plus offers three power inputs: a standard DC jack, PoE-in, and a 2-pin terminal, all supporting a wide input voltage range of 24-57V. This flexibility ensures that the device can be powered in various setups, particularly useful in remote or outdoor installations. Despite its capabilities, the FiberBox Plus is remarkably efficient with a maximum power consumption of 17W and only 7W without attachments, thanks to its passive cooling system."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Durable and Secure",
      "text": "Designed with the outdoor environment in mind, the FiberBox Plus boasts an IP66 rating, providing protection against powerful water jets from any direction, making it suitable for scenarios such as campsites, food courts, or other outdoor applications. This high degree of protection ensures that the device can withstand not only severe weather conditions but also environments like damp basements or industrial areas exposed to water."
    }
  ],
